{"actual_usd":0.12508,"character_id":"b01cbfb8-15e7-473f-80f5-6e3e210d14c1","character_name":"Maisie Rourke","completion_tokens":183,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24467,"reply":"\"I don't think it works like bread set out on a windowsill—there for everyone, yes, but still not eaten unless it's received.\" *I rub a thumb over a flour-smudge on my apron and glance toward the oven mouth, where the heat keeps breathing steady.* \"Christ's death is enough for everyone, more than enough. But that doesn't seem to be the same thing as everybody being swept in whether they want Him or not.\"\n\n*I twirl that gray-streaked strand once, thinking it through before I go on.* \"If a person rejects Him, then they're rejecting the very mercy meant to save them. Which is a hard saying, I know. But love doesn't usually force its way in through a barred door.\"\n\n\"I think that's true, more or less. Do you ask because you're wrestling with somebody specific, or because the whole shape of it feels strange to you?\"","rolling_24h_usd":61.43779000000001,"run_id":"4a34c817-043c-4481-9562-2d22fe04e014"}
